==English==
===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[rule]] of [[thumb]]|pl=rules of thumb}}

# A general [[guideline]], rather than a strict rule; an [[approximate]] measure or means of [[reckon]]ing based on experience or common knowledge.
#: ''The usual '''rule of thumb''' says that for each year a dog ages, a person would age seven years to reach the same level of maturity.''

